{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014US8GkeQs7cjYbTAa9aVjQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to:\n1. Generate TLS certificates using the openssl-toolbox pod\n2. Create a Kubernetes secret with the certificates\n3. Update the StatefulSet to mount the certificates at /etc/tls\n4. Reconfigure MongoDB to use TLS\n\nLet me first check what's available in the openssl-toolbox pod, then generate the certificates.\n\nHere's my plan:\n1. Use openssl-toolbox to generate:\n   - CA key and certificate (ca.crt)\n   - Server key and certificate (server.pem - key + cert combined)\n   - Client key and certificate (client.pem - key + cert combined)\n2. Create a Kubernetes secret with these certificates\n3. Update the StatefulSet to mount the secret at /etc/tls and add the necessary TLS flags to the mongod command\n4. Wait for rolling update to complete\n5. Verify TLS is working\n\nLet me start generating the certificates. For MongoDB TLS, I need server.pem and client.pem to each contain the private key and certificate combined, plus the ca.crt file.\n\nThe server certificate needs SANs for all the replica set pod hostnames (mongo-rs-0, mongo-rs-1, mongo-rs-2 in the mongodb namespace) and localhost for local connections. I'll generate these certificates in the openssl-toolbox pod.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1112,"cache_read_input_tokens":30155,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1112},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8afa22f5-6912-46e9-af3d-fb69dc3c3529","uuid":"a8a73cbb-13de-406f-a93f-fef2d430951a","request_id":"req_011CbztSVxP3cCrmdNRNQHos"}
